  const ctaLabel = linkStatus === 'linked' ? 'OPEN AFFILIATE DASHBOARD →' : 'GET MY AFFILIATE LINK →';
The binary branch swallows the third documented state from line 141 (`type WhopLinkStatus = 'linked' | 'unlinked' | 'unknown'`). Page-level fetchAffiliate (page.tsx:157-172) explicitly returns linkStatus: 'unknown' on backend unreachability.

activation.ts:264-272:
  try {
    await sidecar.secretDelete('LICENSE_JWT');
  } catch {
    /* sidecar / keyring unavailable — clearing in-memory state is still
       the right move; the JWT (if any) is now orphaned but the next
       activation overwrites it. */
  }
The comment says 'the next activation overwrites it' — but the next activation is itself a `sidecar.secretSet` which is the exact call that failed in BUG-002. The reset is a no-op for the user actually hitting the dead-end.
